body.description: Help keep your baby’s skin dry and healthy all night long with Huggies Overnites Baby Diapers! As the #1 Selling Night-Time Diaper*, Overnites night diapers feature a DryTouch Liner with extra absorbency that locks away moisture for up to 12 hours of overnight protection, which can help prevent the need for midnight changes. With a curved shape for up to 100% leak free nighttime protection and a pocketed waistband to help prevent blowouts, Huggies Overnites provide all-night protection and comfort so your baby can have dry nights and restful sleep. These disposable overnight diapers also feature Double Grip Strips for a secure fit, perfect for babies starting to roll and toss during sleep. They also are designed to help provide red-mark free protection around your baby’s legs and have pillowy soft leg cuffs. Plus, a breathable outer cover helps keep your baby's skin dry and comfortable, while Huggies' wetness indicator lets you know if your little one needs a diaper change. Free of fragrance and made with no harsh ingredients, Overnites diapers are perfect for babies with sensitive skin. Huggies Overnites night time diapers feature adorable Disney Winnie the Pooh designs and are available in size 3 (16-28 lbs), size 4 (22-37 lbs), size 5 (27+ lbs), size 6 (35+ lbs) and size 7 (41+ lbs). For daytime protection, try Huggies Little Movers! (*Based on US Nielsen data ending 9/17/2022)

What makes Overnites Huggies' most absorbent diaper? Huggies Overnites baby diapers are ideal for nighttime because they combine dreamy softness with 25% more absorbency than Huggies Snug & Dry diapers. Are Huggies Overnites safe for your delicate baby skin? Absolutely, baby! Huggies overnight baby diapers are hypoallergenic and free of fragrance, lotion and elemental chlorine bleaching to protect your soft, sensitive skin. What size do Huggies Overnites go up to? Our overnight baby diapers offer 4 sizes for your cozy, nighttime convenience, baby: sizes 3 through 7. What do the Double Grip Strips do? Our patented Double Grip Strips are on all Huggies Overnites baby diapers. These special grips help keep your diaper securely in place, no matter what how much you rock & roll in your crib. Do Huggies Overnites diapers expire? There is no shelf life for Huggies Overnites baby diapers.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love using these!
reviews.reviewText: We use these for over a year now for when she sleeping. my daughter pees alot during the night and since switching over to these diapers we have not had any leakage. They are really soft and very absorbent, highly sugguest!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Incredible - don’t hesitate!
reviews.reviewText: I was doing middle of the night diapers for weeks with my “heavily hydrated” kid. No matter what we tried, my baby was waking up in a puddle - disrupting her sleep and mine. The Huggies overnights have been an absolute game changer after being introduced by a friend! My baby started wearing 3’s when she was about 2.5 months and 10lbs. They were big but still worked great. She is sleeping longer stretches and we are waking up dry and happy!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars No leaks, EVER!
reviews.reviewText: We’ve been using the overnights for at least 2 years. They are more expensive than a regular diaper, but we haven’t had a single leak those entire 2 years. The only bit of advice I’d give you is make sure you absolutely change your child’s diaper pretty much immediately after they wake up or else you may have an exploded diaper.

reviews.reviewText: Super absorbent, soft and don't cause any rash. These hold a large amount of pee, and also my baby likes to poop every morning now but it holds that too lol

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Only overnights we use
reviews.reviewText: Sure once in a while it leaks but it’s usually bc we had some crazy extra amount to drink overnight or we put it on not so great. Overall these are the best overnights we have tried over the last two years. Only ones we use. Daytime we use Amazon or used to use luvs bc they work well and good price point. But these are worth it. We also size up slightly bc my daughter is a little thicker and they are fantastic.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great diapers; quality control issues
reviews.reviewText: We have used these diapers with both our kids and love them - however the latest box of Size 5 diapers that I received included inconsistently sized diapers (see picture).

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars No More Leaks!! Read to the end!
reviews.reviewText: These nighttime diapers are a game changer! We only use huggies diapers, and were sizing up for nighttime, but if the boys slept a little later in the morning, they would wake up soaked. We started using these night time diapers, and are still sizing up, and we never have leaks even with sleeping on their tummy. Make sure you are sizing up at least one size, sometimes even two sizes if they are on the cusp of needing daytimes upsized soon (ex. my boys are almost out of size 3s during the day and will be moving to 4s soon, and right now we are in size 5 at night). Even if they feel a little big, and the straps are overlapping, it is okay, just make sure the part around their legs are pulled snug!! Side note, its amazing these last all night because my one boy wakes up to feed throughout the night a few times, and my other two are fed with a feeding tube all night long. So these diapers are HEAVY in the morning!!
